Detailed Description

Namespace General is used to store the commonly used structs and enums.

This module holds the information structures that are used by many modules in IP-Xact parsing that are not otherwise connected to each other.

QString General::getAbsolutePath ( const QString  originalPath,
const QString  relativePath 
)

Get an absolute path of a file.

This function takes original path and uses it as base. Then the relative path is used from the original path to find the correct location of a file. The absolute path to the file is returned. If the relative path contains a file but it is not found null string is returned. Original path may contain a file path or only a directory path but only directory path is used.

Parameters:
originalPath The absolute path that is used as base for relative path
relativePath The relative path that is used to find the file or directory.
Returns:
The absolute path of the target directory/file

QString General::removeWhiteSpace ( QString  str  ) 

removes white spaces from the given QString

This function removes white spaces from the beginning and end of the string and also replaces any embedded whitespaces with characted '_'. If you only want to remove the white spaces from the start and end use QString::trimmed() instead of this.

IP-Xact types used for this function: -Name -NMTOKEN -PortName -ID -IDREF

Parameters:
str A reference to the QString where white spaces are wanted to be removed from.
Returns:
QString containing the string that has been stripped from whitespaces and embedded whitespaces have been replaces with '_'
